@NODE "MBRTest-2.info"

 The 'MBRTest-2' drawer.
 ---------------------

 'MBRTest-2' is a high quality check & test program supplied together with
 a 'Microbotics A1230' accelerator.
 The drawer shows this board and when clicked a magnifying glass comes in
 checking it through. You must also take a look at @{"the 'RamTests' drawer" LINK "RamTests.info"}.

@ENDNODE



@NODE "Megalosound.info"

 The 'Megalosound' drawer.
 -------------------------

 Megalosound is a sampler and sample editor, so I took the sample from the
 original program icon, cut it in half and put it on the drawer icon.

@ENDNODE



@NODE "Modules.info"

 The 'Modules' drawer.
 ---------------------

 A simple ProTracker pattern with some notes on it. I like it better than
 any other 'Modules' drawer icon 8).

@ENDNODE



@NODE "MVK.info"

 The 'MVK' drawer.
 -----------------

 A disk with a magnifying glass that scans the disk for viruses. When
 clicked we see that the disk is infected with an incredibly small virus.
 It could be the one that says: "FUCK"!

@ENDNODE



@NODE "NewMode.dr.info"

 The 'NewMode' drawer.
 ---------------------

 This is my interpretation of the name of the program. NewMode is
 represented by an old dull monitor being transformed into a hypermodern
 multysinc monitor. The actual purpose of the program is explained in the
 chapter: @{"The 'NewMode' icon." LINK "NewMode.info"}.

@ENDNODE



@NODE "Packers.info"

 The 'Packers' drawer.
 ---------------------

 Well, this is just a small version of a @{"MagicWB" LINK "What is MagicWB 2.0?"} dock-brush put on an
 imagedrawer icon. If you wish an extremely simple explanation of a
 packing routine, you ought to read the following chapter, back to front:
 @{"The 'Depackers' drawer." LINK "Depackers.info"} 8).

@ENDNODE



@NODE "Performance1.info"

 The 'Performance1' drawer.
 --------------------------

 A computer with a questionmark on it. It tries to call a question by the
 user:"What the hell is inside this machine?" You'll know the answer if
 you startup one of the programs inside this drawer.

@ENDNODE



@NODE "Performance2.info"

 The 'Performance2' drawer.
 --------------------------

 This is the same as @{"the 'Performance1' drawer" LINK "Performance1.info"}. This one is just for more
 expert users who know what's in this machine, but who want to show off to
 others 8). So, it doesn't call the question by the user, but by a friend.

@ENDNODE



@NODE "Picticon.info"

 The 'Picticon' drawer.
 ----------------------

 The icon visible on the drawer is a tiny version of the standard dull
 DPaint icon which accompanies a picture. When clicked it reveals a nice
 @{"MagicWB" LINK "What is MagicWB 2.0?"} icon of the same picture. It's just the same as what 'Picticon'
 does: transforming your picture into a @{"MagicWB" LINK "What is MagicWB 2.0?"} icon.

@ENDNODE



